'''光氫'''（{{lang-en|photohydrogen}}）是在人造或自然[[光|光]]的幫助下產生的[[氫|氫]]。這就是樹的葉子如何將[[水|水]]分子分裂成[[質子|質子]]（氫離子）、[[電子|電子]]（產生[[碳水化合物|碳水化合物]]）和[[氧|氧]]（作為廢物釋放到空氣中）<ref>[https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/sciencenow/3210/01.html NOVA scienceNOW] {{Wayback|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/sciencenow/3210/01.html |date=20100217171202 }} - A 14 minute video of the ''[[Nova_(American_TV_series)|NOVA]]'' broadcast about hydrogen [[fuel_cell|fuel cell]] cars that aired on [[Public_Broadcasting_Service|PBS]], July 26, 2005. Hosted by [[Robert_Krulwich|Robert Krulwich]] with guests, [[Ray_Magliozzi|Ray]] and [[Tom_Magliozzi|Tom Magliozzi]], the ''[[Car_Talk|Car Talk]]'' brothers.</ref>。光氫也可以通過[[紫外線|紫外線]]使水光解離而產生。

有時在通過使用諸如[[細菌|細菌]]或[[藻類|藻類]]之類的[[微生物|微生物]]從陽光中獲取[[可再生能源|可再生能源]]的背景下討論光氫。這些生物利用[[氫化酶|氫化酶]]產生氫，氫酶將水分解反應產生的[[質子|質子]]轉化為氫氣，然後收集該氫氣並將其用作[[生物燃料|生物燃料]]<ref name=powerplant>{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/news/technology/0,1282,54456,00.html |title=Algae: Power Plant of the Future? |accessdate=2006-09-17 |last=Gartner |first=John |date=2002-08-19 |publisher=Wired |pages=1 |archive-date=2012-02-21 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65ceJF1p7?url=http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2002/08/54456 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=swamp>{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/10.04/mustread.html?pg=5 |title=It Came From the Swamp |accessdate=2006-09-17 |last=Mechanic |first=Michael |date=April 2002 |publisher=Wired |pages=1 |archive-date=2012-02-21 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65ceLhGvr?url=http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/10.04/mustread.html?pg=5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

